Compile and Run:
    gcc -o server server.c
    gcc -o client client.c


Sources used:
    https://www.cs.dartmouth.edu/~campbell/cs50/socketprogramming.html -- basis of the forking
    https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4217037/catch-ctrl-c-in-c -- Handle ctrl c gracefully

Current Problems:
    - Server keeps sending multiple of the same file contents after GET is correctly called
    - After get is correctly called, you have to send the same command twice before it works
    - server exits twice and closes socket twice

